        "id" : "d8398ae8-9bec-414c-9493-8ce88bf9f99a",
        "parentId" : "738b50bf-1688-4324-806d-befec87370e2",
        "authorId" : "aca8a2c5-2545-4cc5-9149-eedb61eeb6f4",
        "body" : "I don't have any experience with submitting a condo-forge application, so I may not understand the question. Numpy is certainly required in order to run the nexusformat API. If the problem is that it is specifically imported in `setup.py`, that may be a historic relic from a previous stage of its development. I have checked that the following two lines can be removed from `setup.py` without causing any problems with pytest:\r\n```\r\nimport pkg_resources\r\npkg_resources.require('numpy')\r\n```",
        "createdAt" : "2019-09-16T15:18:25Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2019-09-17T09:37:19Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "aca8a2c5-2545-4cc5-9149-eedb61eeb6f4",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "2d0f2f95-dfc6-4e47-ac6c-575c0f483f74",
        "parentId" : "738b50bf-1688-4324-806d-befec87370e2",
        "authorId" : "dc1cfabe-d5ff-47d1-862d-2ac96e9bd158",
        "body" : "The conda recipes make a distinction between build- (`requirements.host`) and run-time (`requirements.run`) dependencies. The former are necessary to ensure `python setup.py install` can be executed, while the latter are required to ensure the installation itself can be run, and are therefore also used to run the test block.\r\n\r\n@scopatz I don't mind attaching a patch that removes these two lines... let me know if this necessary.",
        "createdAt" : "2019-09-16T15:37:47Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2019-09-17T09:37:19Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "dc1cfabe-d5ff-47d1-862d-2ac96e9bd158",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "267068b5-4c60-45af-97f0-28188f569a70",
        "parentId" : "738b50bf-1688-4324-806d-befec87370e2",
        "authorId" : "d838053f-6fcd-47a0-a593-accf1cf846b0",
        "body" : "There is no need to patch it here but, if you have time, it's worth making a PR upstream so it can be removed in the next version.\r\n\r\nIf you do, `COPYING` should be added to the `MANIFEST.in` file so the licence file is included in the tarball on PyPI (technically a requirement of BSD-3-Clause).",
        "createdAt" : "2019-09-17T07:33:27Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2019-09-17T09:37:19Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "d838053f-6fcd-47a0-a593-accf1cf846b0",
